# No Chakra `<Icon>` wrapper for react-icons

`react-icons` don't support `forwardRef`. Chakra v3's `<Icon>` (`chakra(svg)`) passes refs, causing console warnings.

## Rules

- Never wrap react-icons inside `<Icon>`: use them directly
- For sizing, pass `size` prop: `<LuPlay size={20} />`
- For color/responsive sizing, wrap in `<Box as="span">` with `fontSize` and `color`
- `<Icon asChild>` with raw `<svg>` elements is fine (they accept refs)

```tsx
// BAD
<Icon boxSize={5} color="text.subtle">
  <LuRadar />
</Icon>

// GOOD - direct usage
<LuRadar size={20} />

// GOOD - with Chakra styling
<Box as="span" color="text.subtle" fontSize="20px" lineHeight="1">
  <LuRadar />
</Box>

// GOOD - responsive sizing
<Box as="span" color="text.subtle" fontSize={{ base: "16px", md: "20px" }}>
  <LuRadar />
</Box>

// OK - raw SVG (not react-icons)
<Icon asChild boxSize="18px">
  <svg>...</svg>
</Icon>
```
